Review title: A comfortable stay in a quiet suburb nestled away from the busy CBD which feels like a community.
Positive review:
This is my "go-to" home away from home if I need to stay near my essential work because it is nestled in a quiet area which feels like a community, away from the hustle and bustle of Sydney CBD, but still close to the CBD.
Facilities are clean and new and never a problem with the showers unlike other one or two hostels in other areas, where taps are broken or hard to adjust water temperature.
The bed mattress on the beds are soft and comfortable.
Totally pest free which means it is cleaned well 
This building is well maintained under good and remarkable management and staff 
Thank you for a comfortable stay.

Thank you excellent management and staff for a lovely stay.
Comfortable beds.
Clean and I mostly like the well ventilated building with fresh air coming in the hallways and rooms, so there is no smell and fresh air.
Staff are accommodating but still following protocols. Professional

Own private bathroom. Very small though. 
Good for when you need a place to just sleep and rest. You get what you pay for.
Negative review:

Review title: Management shoved my 10 year old daughter out the way and said 'move!!!' ar her ð¡
Positive review: The room was ok for the cost which we knew was budget.
Negative review:
A fine for using a hair-dryer? Are you serious!!?! That was NOT on the booking information or part of my contract checking in. If I book a room with a private bathroom I expect to be able to get ready in it.

Also the guy in the reception, no eye contact, no hi when you arrive etc. You end up feeling like a ghost. That was fine... He did try and be nice in the end but it all felt really weird.

What wasn't fine was the other guy who I don't believe is the owner shoving my 10 year old daughter out the way and blasting 'move!!!' At her while she was waiting outside reception for somebody to arrive and check us in. Plenty of room to move around a young girl, totally inappropriate and rude to speak to a child like this who was standing there patiently with more respect than this man could ever have. I told him I wasn't going to proceed with thr booking and wanted a refund because I will not have my child spoken to like that and he got argumentative about ne cancelling. That was after I kindly told him that no way to speak to a little girl you should probably apologise. No apology just more rudeness. Some kind of unacceptable grump not related to us but I tell you one thing he's lucky my partner was not there to see it.

Also the entry upstairs looks like a prison with ugly bars, just not family friendly at all I would never bring kids here, we couldn't enjoy the room because we didn't want to disturb anyone even with the TV down low, couldn't use the hair dryer and despite advertising it there was no wifi so I couldn't do anything I needed to do at night time while the children slept.

Really not hard to make this place or the stay a little better. I hope management read this and up their welcoming skills, a slightly harder shove and yes I would have called the police in and pressed assault charges.
Property reply: First we refute the allegation of shoving of your daughter. Obviously if someone speak with your daughter that way it's unacceptable. The staffs involved had been warned. Potts Point and Kingscross are one of the busiest area in Sydney, especially during World Pride Weeks and football nights. We mentioned quiet time after 10pm during check in but we cannot prevent outside noises, it's beyond our control. 
As for our room size, again we are a boutique hotel in one of the busiest area in Sydney. Our room size are similar with other surrounding boutique hotels. Of couse, if you compare our room sizes with 5 stars hotel in the CBD or hotels in the rural area, then yes our rooms are smaller than them. But please don't forget you are only paying a fraction of the price.
